                            <comment id="14637024" author="enigmacurry" created="Wed, 22 Jul 2015 14:52:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stefania_alborghetti&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stefania_alborghetti&quot;&gt;stefania_alborghetti&lt;/a&gt; fyi this is still hanging your job presently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14637025" author="benedict" created="Wed, 22 Jul 2015 14:53:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, there isn&apos;t actually a good reason for it not to die here. So I wonder what non-daemon threads are running keeping the process up. It hasn&apos;t spun up any workers or anything by this point. Are the Java Driver&apos;s threads non-daemon?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However we can enforce it to sysexit in the event of any exception in the main thread quite easily.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14637366" author="benedict" created="Wed, 22 Jul 2015 18:26:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve pushed a trivial &quot;fix&quot; to this &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/belliottsmith/cassandra/tree/9864&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; that force-quits if we encounter an exception on the main thread.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14637433" author="enigmacurry" created="Wed, 22 Jul 2015 18:53:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14637784" author="benedict" created="Wed, 22 Jul 2015 22:41:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks. Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14637939" author="stefania" created="Wed, 22 Jul 2015 23:52:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
